<section class="lg:py-[112px] py-[48px]">
  <div class="max-w-screen-2xl lg:px-20 px-[24px] mx-auto">
    <div class="lg:mb-[80px] mb-[24px] overflow-hidden">
      <h2
        data-aos="fade-up"
        class="text-center lg:text-[52px] text-[32px] lg:leading-[56px] leading-[36px] font-black font-ppradio text-textPrimary"
      >
        Frequently asked questions
      </h2>
      <p
        class="lg:text-[20px] text-[18px] lg:leading-[24px] leading-[22px] text-textSecondary font-figtree text-center mt-[16px]"
      >
        Got questions? We’ve answered the most common ones below
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-[40px] gap-[20px]">
      <div class="space-y-[20px] column">
        <div class="p-[20px] rounded-[20px] bg-white acd-shadow">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px] accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            How much does a bespoke ring cost?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px]"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              This depends entirely on the type/quality of materials and gemstones you want to use, as well as the complexity of the design. People usually spend at least £1000.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-[20px] rounded-[20px] bg-white acd-shadow">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px] accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            How long does the bespoke process take?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px]"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              The timeline for crafting a custom engagement ring depends on the jeweller, the availability of materials, and the complexity of the design. It's always a good idea to check with the jeweller about their current lead times before committing. Typically, you can expect the process to take between 6 to 12 weeks, but this can vary based on specific requirements.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-[20px] rounded-[20px] bg-white acd-shadow">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px] accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            What’s the ideal budget for a custom engagement ring?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px]"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              The ideal budget for a custom engagement ring really depends on the design you have in mind! The best approach is to share your budget and preferred style with your jeweller, who will then guide you on the materials and gemstones that suit your price range. A skilled jeweller will always collaborate with you to create a design that aligns with both your vision and budget. Naturally, a larger budget will provide more flexibility in terms of design and gemstone options, but beautiful creations can be made at various price points.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-[20px] column">
        <div class="p-[20px] rounded-[20px] bg-white acd-shadow">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px] accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            How do I know if the final design will meet my expectations?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px]"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              You'll be fully involved throughout the entire design process. Your jeweller will work closely with you from the start, presenting design options based on your preferences. Once you've chosen your favourite, the creation begins. You'll receive regular updates as the ring takes shape, ensuring you're happy with every step of the process and that the final piece aligns with your vision.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-[20px] rounded-[20px] bg-white acd-shadow">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px] accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            Will I get to see a design before the ring is made?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px]"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              Absolutely! When working with an independent designer, the process always begins by creating and finalising a design together. Many jewellers are open to making adjustments during the creation process if you have a change of heart. However, it's important to note that changes at this stage may come with additional costs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-[20px] rounded-[20px] bg-white acd-shadow">
          <button
            class="cursor-pointer w-full flex justify-between items-center gap-2 text-left font-normal text-textPrimary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px] accordion-btn p-0"
            aria-expanded="false"
          >
            How involved can I be in the design process?
            <span class="icon text-xl leading-[24px] text-[30px]">+</span>
          </button>
          <div
            class="accordion-content max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-all duration-300 font-normal text-textSecondary font-figtree leading-[18px] lg:leading-[22px] text-base lg:text-[18px]"
          >
            <p class="mt-2">
              We encourage you to be as involved as possible! The design process is an exciting and creative experience. Our jewellers love collaborating with clients to craft unique, custom designs, and it’s often one of the most rewarding parts of their work. You’ll have the chance to discuss your vision in detail and work closely with the jeweller to bring your ideas to life. Rest assured, no design will be finalised without your full approval, ensuring the end result is exactly what you envisioned.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script is:inline>
  if (typeof window !== "undefined") {
    const buttons = document.querySelectorAll(".accordion-btn");

    buttons.forEach((btn) => {
      btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
        const column = btn.closest(".column");
        const content = btn.nextElementSibling;
        const icon = btn.querySelector(".icon");

        column.querySelectorAll(".accordion-content").forEach((el) => {
          if (el !== content) {
            el.style.maxHeight = null;
            const otherBtn = el.previousElementSibling;
            if (otherBtn) {
              otherBtn.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "false");
              const otherIcon = otherBtn.querySelector(".icon");
              if (otherIcon) otherIcon.textContent = "+";
            }
          }
        });

        if (content.style.maxHeight) {
          content.style.maxHeight = null;
          btn.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "false");
          if (icon) icon.textContent = "+";
        } else {
          content.style.maxHeight = content.scrollHeight + "px";
          btn.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "true");
          if (icon) icon.textContent = "–";
        }
      });
    });

    window.addEventListener("resize", () => {
      document.querySelectorAll(".accordion-content").forEach((el) => {
        if (el.style.maxHeight) {
          el.style.maxHeight = el.scrollHeight + "px";
        }
      });
    });
  }
</script>
